<p style="text-align: left;">
 
<span style="font-size: 25px;"><strong>1931-04-03 &#8211; The Estes Park Trail &#8211; Footbridge built at Ed Wilds Harding Heights</strong></span>




<br>
<br>
<span style="font-size: 20px;"><i><strong>Transcription</strong></i></span> 

<br>
<span style="font-size: 22px;"><i>Berthoud Dale Briefs</i></span> 


<br>
<i>"There have been two bridges constructed over the Big Thompson river this winter, one at the small dam near the Cotner College ranch to give a nearer entrance to the Fred Neville ranch, also at the Nugget Springs ranch Messrs. Bean and Palmer have made a dude ranch out of the Jackson place at Montrose. A foot bridge is under construction at Ed Wild’s place at Harding Heights about 10 miles east of Estes village. Mr. Wild expects to erect a store on the highway across the river from his ranch to which the bridge will lead."</i>


<br><br>
<span style="font-size: 20px;"><i><strong>People</strong></i></span> 
<br>






Ed Wild


<br>





<br>
<span style="font-size: 20px;"><i><strong>Details</strong></i></span> 


<br>
<i>Date: 1931-04-03</i>


<br>
<i>Location: USA, Colorado, Estes Park</i>





<br>
